<p> </p>
<p><strong>Itinerary </strong></p>
<p><strong>Day 1 (Wednesday) </strong>Fly to Geneva airport. Transfer by coach to the <a data-udi="umb://document/98e5917964c04bbf9caa7f5e69e9874e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/98e5917964c04bbf9caa7f5e69e9874e}" title="Hotel Sapiniere">Hotel La Sapinière</a> in <a data-udi="umb://document/2735e2389f7c411cb3061226ce7548d1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2735e2389f7c411cb3061226ce7548d1}" title="Chamonix">Chamonix</a> (approx. 1 hour).</p>
<p><strong>Day 2 (Thursday)</strong> Half day guided biking, including the bike hire. Follow the lead of your instructor through winding forests and over pretty streams. Earn your tasty evening meal with some uphill pedalling too!</p>
<p><strong>Day 3 (Friday) </strong>A free day. Join the excursion to <a data-udi="umb://document/59d85c3607bf4fc5a291361000fe9db0" href="/{localLink:umb://document/59d85c3607bf4fc5a291361000fe9db0}" title="Lake Annecy">Annecy</a> and visit the beautiful old town (optional). Or if you’d prefer to stay in Chamonix, explore the extensive walking trails using the Multipa (extra charge) giving access to all lifts.</p>
<p><strong>Day 4 (Saturday) </strong>Experience the excitement of white water rafting in Chamonix! (The session is for those over 10 years of age). The thrilling morning will require a calm afternoon!</p>
<p><strong>Day 5 (Sunday) </strong>A free day with the choice to explore the picturesque town or why not go parapenting to savour the glorious views from the air (optional)?</p>
<p><strong>Day 6 (Monday)</strong> A Free day. Why not join in the Three Countries Tour excursion or explore the walking trails, then take the rack and pinion railway up to the Mer de Glace and spend an unforgettable night in the <a data-udi="umb://document/7c89165bd6bc4b71a5a7b533930f895e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7c89165bd6bc4b71a5a7b533930f895e}" title="Refuge de Montenvers - Overnight Glacier Experience">Refuge du Montenvers</a> (optional)?</p>
<p><strong>Day 7 (Tuesday) </strong>Spend half a day with a qualified walking guide, exploring the paths that you may not have yet discovered. Listen to tales of Chamonix’s legends and benefit from the knowledge of your guide on the local flora and fauna.</p>
<p><strong>Day 8 (Wednesday) </strong>Transfer back to Geneva airport for your return journey home (approx. 1 hour).</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>What's Included </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Return scheduled flights from the UK </li>
<li>Return airport transfers</li>
<li>7 nights in 3.5 star <a data-udi="umb://document/98e5917964c04bbf9caa7f5e69e9874e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/98e5917964c04bbf9caa7f5e69e9874e}" title="Hotel Sapiniere">Hotel La Sapinière</a> run by Inghams staff </li>
<li>Daily continental breakfast, daily packed lunch, afternoon tea and freshly baked cake, 3 course buffet evening meal with wine, tea &amp; coffee on 5 nights</li>
<li>Services of an Inghams rep</li>
<li>Session of rafting</li>
<li>Guided bike ride</li>
<li>Guided hike</li>
<li>Free use of local bus and train travel in <a data-udi="umb://document/2735e2389f7c411cb3061226ce7548d1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2735e2389f7c411cb3061226ce7548d1}" title="Chamonix">Chamonix</a></li>
<li>Resort card </li>
<li>Walking opportunities</li>
</ul>
